    <p class="c6"><span class="c7">1. HTML (HyperText Markup Language):</span></p>
    <ul class="c8 lst-kix_73enm78wsupk-0 start">
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0"><span class="c2"><b>Description:</b> The standard markup language used to create web pages.</span></li>
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0"><span class="c2"><b>Role:</b> Defines the structure of web content, using elements such as headings, paragraphs, links, images, and more.</span></li>
    </ul>
    <p class="c5"><span class="c1"></span></p>
    <p class="c6"><span class="c7">2. CSS (Cascading Style Sheets):</span></p>
    <ul class="c8 lst-kix_r0f4mw81x6k6-0 start">
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0"><span class="c2"><b>Description:</b> A style sheet language used for describing the presentation of a document written in HTML or XML.</span></li>
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0"><span class="c2"><b>Role:</b> Controls the layout and appearance of the web pages, including design elements like colors, fonts, and spacing.</span></li>
    </ul>

    <p class="c6"><span class="c7">3. JavaScript:</span></p>
    <ul class="c8 lst-kix_r0f4mw81x6k6-0 start">
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0"><span class="c2"><b>Description:</b>A programming language that enables interactive web pages.</span></li>
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0"><span class="c2"><b>Role:</b> Enhances user engagement through dynamic content, interactive forms, animations, and more.</span></li>
    </ul>

    <p class="c6"><span class="c7">4. Front-End Frameworks and Libraries:</span></p>
    <ul class="c8 lst-kix_r0f4mw81x6k6-0 start">
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0"><span class="c2"><b>Examples:</b> React, Angular, Vue.js.</span></li>
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0"><span class="c2"><b>Role:</b> Simplify the development of complex user interfaces and improve code management.</span></li>
    </ul>

    <p class="c6"><span class="c7">5. Back-End Technologies:</span></p>
    <ul class="c8 lst-kix_r0f4mw81x6k6-0 start">
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0"><span class="c2"><b>Languages:</b> PHP, Python, Ruby, Java, Node.js.</span></li>
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0"><span class="c2"><b>Role:</b> Handle server-side logic, database interactions, user authentication, and data processing.</span></li>
    </ul>

    <p class="c6"><span class="c7">6. Databases:</span></p>
    <ul class="c8 lst-kix_r0f4mw81x6k6-0 start">
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0"><span class="c2"><b>Types:</b> SQL (MySQL, PostgreSQL), NoSQL (MongoDB, Redis).</span></li>
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0"><span class="c2"><b>Role:</b> Store and manage data used by web applications.</span></li>
    </ul>

    <p class="c6"><span class="c7">7. APIs (Application Programming Interfaces):</span></p>
    <ul class="c8 lst-kix_r0f4mw81x6k6-0 start">
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0"><span class="c2"><b>Description:</b> Interfaces that allow different software systems to communicate.</span></li>
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0"><span class="c2"><b>Role:</b> Enable integration with third-party services, such as payment gateways, social media platforms, and cloud services.</span></li>
    </ul>

    <p class="c6"><span class="c7">8. Version Control Systems:</span></p>
    <ul class="c8 lst-kix_r0f4mw81x6k6-0 start">
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0"><span class="c2"><b>Examples:</b> Git, Subversion.</span></li>
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0"><span class="c2"><b>Role:</b> Track and manage changes to the codebase, facilitating collaboration and maintaining a history of code changes.</span></li>
    </ul>

